A 10-year-old boy was bit by an off-duty Largo police dog in Tarpon Springs on Tuesday, the Tarpon Springs Police Department reported. Tarpon Springs police said in a news release that they received a call just before 4:30 p.m. Tuesday about a dog bite. When officers arrived at the scene, they learned that “an off duty Largo Police Department Canine was accidentally released from his fenced-in yard area and bit a 10-year-old juvenile,” a news release from the Tarpon Springs department states. Police said the boy’s father took him to the hospital and the boy was in stable condition. This is a developing story. Stay with tampabay.com for updates.